tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function with possible acute or chronic kidney disease. Low total COâ and elevated chloride may indicate metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) support renal involvement but no clear evidence of infection. Low HbA1c and normal glucose exclude diabetes. Recommend nephrology evaluation and further assessment of renal function and acid-base status.
